Located within the premier western precinct, this is a strategic development site that benefits from the significant surrounding infrastructure including the new Royal Adelaide Hospital, China Town and The Adelaide Central Markets.  With a total site area of 4,803sqm* and Capital City zoning, the opportunities are endless. Key investment highlights include:

• 4,803 sqm* site area over two titles
• Frontages of 46.6m* to Grote Street and 12.2m to West Tce
• Access also available from Gouger Street
• Three level existing showroom of 3,730sqm  
• Zoned Capital City allowing up to 53 metres (S.T.C.C)
• Holding income from car park agreement 

The Vendor has provided clear instruction that this property must be sold. Act quickly so as not to miss out.

CBRE Capital Markets is thrilled to be favored with instructions for the sale of 215 Grote Street, Adelaide currently under a long-term lease to national furniture retailer Early Settler. 215 Grote Street is exceptionally well-situated to the West of the Adelaide CBD, in an established commercial precinct in very close proximity to Chinatown, Adelaide Central Markets, West Terrace & just 900m* from the Adelaide BioMedical Precinct.

Underpinning the exceptional location is the underlying land value with a total site area of 2,787sqm* within a flexible zoning. The building consists of three levels with varied improvements including showroom, offices, warehousing & café.

We further highlight the below key features of the property which is the perfect definition of an ‘invest now, develop later’ property:

- Net rental of $531,726pa*
- Leased to ESR Group Holdings Pty Ltd trading as Early Settler with over 50 stores across Australia & New Zealand
- 5-year lease term expiring 31st October 2024 with further 5-year option
- Site area of 2,787sqm* and GLA of 3,685sqm*
- Flexible Capital City zoning in the City of Adelaide allowing development up to 53m*
- Two Certificates of Title with three street frontages 
- CPI rental increases annually
- Redevelopment Clause within the lease with 18-month notice period
- Tenant pays all outgoings including Land Tax on a single-holding basis

As any Adelaidian would know the iconic building at 221-225 Flinders Street, Adelaide has been the home of one of Adelaide’s most recognizable businesses in The South Australian German Club. This multiple story building has been utilised as a function hall/restaurant/bar in its 105 years of occupancy with the existing improvements being constructed in 1970. 

The property presents the below characteristics sure to appeal to the astute owner occupier, investor or developer:

- Functional and prominent improvements of 2,311sqm* gross  building area
- Three story building with basement and mixture of lift and stair access throughout
- 16.15m* frontage to Flinders and Ifould Streets
- 943sqm* site area
- Flexible Capital City Zoning allowing up to 53m*
- Offered with vacant possession therefore ready for refurbishment, redevelopment (STCC) or occupation*
